# Semgrep ignore patterns
#
# The untrusted-pr.yml workflow intentionally uses pull_request_target
# with checkout of PR code. This is safe because:
#   1. No PR code is executed (no build scripts, no dependency installs)
#   2. safe-scan only passes checkout to TruffleHog (a prebuilt action)
#   3. instruction-file-guard only runs `git diff --name-only` (read-only)
#   4. Both jobs use persist-credentials: false
#   5. Neither job has access to repository secrets
#
# Semgrep's pull-request-target-code-checkout rule flags this pattern
# generically but the specific usage here is audited and safe.
# See: https://securitylab.github.com/research/github-actions-preventing-pwn-requests/
.github/workflows/untrusted-pr.yml
